# Raspberry Pi Notes

## Introduction

Raspberry Pi is a small, affordable computer designed to help people
learn programming, electronics, and computing. It looks like a small
circuit board but works like a normal computer.

## What Raspberry Pi Can Do

-   Run a full operating system
-   Connect to a monitor, keyboard, and mouse
-   Browse the internet
-   Play videos and music
-   Run programming languages such as Python, JavaScript, and C
-   Connect sensors, LEDs, motors, and other hardware
-   Build projects like robots, home automation systems, and servers

## Why Raspberry Pi Is Popular

-   Low cost
-   Uses very little power
-   Easy to learn
-   Supports many programming languages
-   Large community and documentation
-   Works well for learning electronics and creating DIY projects

## Important Components

-   CPU for processing
-   RAM for memory
-   USB ports for keyboard and mouse
-   HDMI port for display
-   GPIO pins for connecting hardware
-   MicroSD card slot for storage
-   Power input for running the device

## Operating System

The most common operating system is Raspberry Pi OS. It is simple,
lightweight, and built for learning.

## Common Uses

-   Home server
-   Media center
-   Learning programming
-   Smart home projects
-   Robotics
-   IoT projects
-   Game emulation
-   Teaching computing concepts

## GPIO Pins

GPIO pins allow you to control electronic devices. They let Raspberry Pi
interact with the physical world by sending signals to components like
LEDs, sensors, and motors.

## Recommended Models

-   Raspberry Pi 4
-   Raspberry Pi 3 Model B+
-   Raspberry Pi Zero 2 W for small projects

## Final Summary

Raspberry Pi is a powerful mini-computer used for learning and building
projects. It is simple to use, flexible, and perfect for programmers,
students, and hobbyists who want to understand computers or create
real-world solutions.
